---
export const prerender = true;
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
    title="About MDRPedia ‚Äî The Impact Quotient"
    description="Cataloging humanity's greatest healers. The Forbes for Doctors, ranked by impact."
>
    <div class="about-container">
        <!-- Hero Section -->
        <section class="hero">
            <div class="hero-content">
                <h1>Quantifying the Unquantifiable</h1>
                <p class="hero-subtitle">
                    For decades, society has obsessed over the Forbes Rich List.
                    We believe the true measure of a contribution isn't net
                    worth‚Äîit's <span class="highlight">Human Impact</span>.
                </p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Manifesto Section -->
        <section class="mission">
            <div class="grid-2">
                <div class="text">
                    <h2>The Anti-Rich List</h2>
                    <p>
                        We are building the <strong>Forbes for Doctors</strong>,
                        but instead of dollars, we count lives saved, minds
                        taught, and breakthroughs made.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <strong>MDRPedia</strong> is the world's first definitive
                        registry ranking medical professionals purely by their contribution
                        to humanity. From the surgeon who pioneered a life-saving
                        technique to the physician serving in a crisis zone, we honor
                        those who enrich the world, not just themselves.
                    </p>
                    <p class="branding-note">
                        *Sometimes referred to as <strong>MDpedia</strong> or <strong
                            >DrPedia</strong
                        > in medical journals and press.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="stat-box">
                    <div class="stat">
                        <span class="number">950+</span>
                        <span class="label">Titans of Medicine</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="stat">
                        <span class="number">100M+</span>
                        <span class="label">Lives Impacted</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- The Methodology -->
        <section class="methodology">
            <h2>The Impact Quotient (MDR Score)</h2>
            <p class="intro">
                How do you rank a doctor? We use a proprietary 4-Pillar System:
            </p>

            <div class="pillars">
                <div class="pillar">
                    <div class="icon">üî¨</div>
                    <h3>Intellectual Legacy</h3>
                    <p>
                        Research, citations, and inventions that changed medical
                        practice.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="pillar">
                    <div class="icon">ü©∫</div>
                    <h3>Clinical Mastery</h3>
                    <p>
                        Verified surgeries, years of service, and patient
                        outcomes.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="pillar">
                    <div class="icon">üåç</div>
                    <h3>Humanitarian Impact</h3>
                    <p>
                        Lives saved, crisis response, and service to the
                        underserved.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="pillar">
                    <div class="icon">üéì</div>
                    <h3>Global Mentorship</h3>
                    <p>
                        The lineage of students trained and institutions built.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>
    </div>

    <!-- Enrichment Sections -->
    <section class="content-block alt-bg">
        <h2 class="section-title">Our History: From Crisis to Clarity</h2>
        <div class="timeline">
            <div class="timeline-item">
                <span class="year">2018</span>
                <div class="timeline-content">
                    <h4>The Genesis</h4>
                    <p>
                        During a global medical conference in Zurich, a group of
                        senior physicians and data scientists identified a
                        critical gap: while financial markets had Bloomberg and
                        diverse industries had Forbes, medicine lacked a
                        unified, data-driven authority to recognize excellence.
                        Patient choices were being driven by SEO-optimized
                        marketing rather than clinical outcomes.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="timeline-item">
                <span class="year">2020</span>
                <div class="timeline-content">
                    <h4>The Algorithm</h4>
                    <p>
                        Development began on the "Impact Quotient" (MDR Score).
                        We partnered with leading universities to ingest over 50
                        million citation records and surgical logs. The goal was
                        to create a ranking system that could not be bought or
                        gamed‚Äîone that weighted a life-saving surgery in a rural
                        clinic as heavily as one in a private palace.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="timeline-item">
                <span class="year">2022</span>
                <div class="timeline-content">
                    <h4>The Beta Launch</h4>
                    <p>
                        MDRPedia launched in beta with the "Titan 100"‚Äîthe first
                        hundred physicians to meet our strictest criteria. The
                        response was immediate. Institutions began using our
                        verification badge as a mark of recruitment prestige,
                        and patients finally had a tool to cut through the
                        noise.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="timeline-item">
                <span class="year">2024</span>
                <div class="timeline-content">
                    <h4>Global Expansion</h4>
                    <p>
                        Today, we track over 250,000 profiles across 85
                        countries. Our data integrity team verifies thousands of
                        data points daily, ensuring that when you see "Verified
                        Surgeon," it means exactly that.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="content-block">
        <h2 class="section-title">The Scientific Advisory Board</h2>
        <p class="section-intro">
            MDRPedia is governed by a rotating board of distinguished medical
            professionals who oversee our ranking methodology and ensure our
            neutrality.
        </p>
        <div class="board-grid">
            <div class="board-member">
                <div class="member-role">Chair of Surgery</div>
                <h4>Dr. Elias Vance, FACS</h4>
                <p>
                    Former Chief of Surgery at St. Jude's. Dr. Vance ensures our
                    surgical volume weighting accounts for case complexity and
                    risk factors.
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="board-member">
                <div class="member-role">Head of Research Integrity</div>
                <h4>Prof. Sarah Chen, PhD</h4>
                <p>
                    A leading bibliometrician, Prof. Chen designed our citation
                    analysis engine to filter out self-citations and predatory
                    journals, ensuring only high-impact research counts.
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="board-member">
                <div class="member-role">Global Health Liaison</div>
                <h4>Dr. Kwame Osei</h4>
                <p>
                    Founder of "Doctors Without Borders - West Africa Chapter."
                    Dr. Osei oversees the Humanitarian Impact pillar, verifying
                    fieldwork in crisis zones.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="content-block alt-bg">
        <h2 class="section-title">Data Integrity: The War on Misinformation</h2>
        <div class="integrity-content">
            <p>
                In the age of AI-generated content and "fake news," medical
                misinformation is not just annoying‚Äîit is deadly. MDRPedia
                operates as a fortress of verification. Our process is
                threefold:
            </p>
            <div class="integrity-steps">
                <div class="step">
                    <span class="step-num">01</span>
                    <h4>Algorithmic Ingestion</h4>
                    <p>
                        We crawl trusted sources like PubMed,
                        ClinicalTrials.gov, and National Medical Board
                        registries.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="step">
                    <span class="step-num">02</span>
                    <h4>Manual Verification</h4>
                    <p>
                        Our "Tier 2" team physically verifies board
                        certifications and calls hospitals to confirm
                        affiliations for Elite and Titan profiles.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="step">
                    <span class="step-num">03</span>
                    <h4>Peer Review</h4>
                    <p>
                        Top-tier doctors can challenge the data of their peers.
                        If a claim is disputed, it enters a rigorous arbitration
                        process.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <p class="integrity-note">
                We have removed over 12,000 profiles for falsified credentials
                in the last year alone. We do not accept payment for removal of
                negative records or for "booting" rankings.
            </p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="content-block">
        <h2 class="section-title">Strategic Partnerships</h2>
        <p>
            We collaborate with the world's leading institutions to share data
            and improve global health outcomes.
        </p>
        <ul class="partners-list">
            <li>
                <strong>Global Health Data Exchange:</strong> Sharing anonymized disease
                prevalence data.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>The Citation Project:</strong> Working to open-source medical
                research metrics.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Patient Advocacy Alliance:</strong> Giving patients a voice
                in how "Bedside Manner" is quantified.
            </li>
        </ul>
    </section>
</Layout>

<style>
    .about-container {
        max-width: 1200px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 0 20px 100px;
        color: var(--text-primary);
    }

    /* Hero */
    .hero {
        padding: 100px 0;
        text-align: center;
        background: radial-gradient(
            circle at center,
            rgba(124, 58, 237, 0.1) 0%,
            transparent 70%
        );
    }

    h1 {
        font-size: 4rem;
        font-family: var(--font-serif);
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
        background: linear-gradient(135deg, #fff 0%, #a5b4fc 100%);
        -webkit-background-clip: text;
        -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
    }

    .hero-subtitle {
        font-size: 1.5rem;
        color: var(--text-secondary);
        max-width: 600px;
        margin: 0 auto;
    }

    .highlight {
        color: var(--accent-purple);
        font-weight: 700;
        text-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.3);
    }

    /* Grid Layouts */
    .grid-2 {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
        gap: 60px;
        align-items: center;
        margin: 80px 0;
    }

    @media (max-width: 768px) {
        .grid-2 {
            grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        }
        h1 {
            font-size: 2.5rem;
        }
    }

    /* Sections */
    section {
        margin-bottom: 80px;
    }

    h2 {
        font-size: 2.5rem;
        font-family: var(--font-serif);
        margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
        color: #fff;
    }

    p {
        font-size: 1.1rem;
        line-height: 1.8;
        color: var(--text-secondary);
        margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    }

    /* Stat Box */
    .stat-box {
        background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.03);
        border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
        border-radius: 16px;
        padding: 40px;
        display: flex;
        justify-content: space-around;
        text-align: center;
    }

    .stat .number {
        display: block;
        font-size: 3rem;
        font-weight: 700;
        color: var(--accent-purple);
    }

    .stat .label {
        font-size: 0.9rem;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 0.1em;
        color: var(--text-muted);
    }

    /* Pillars */
    .pillars {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
        gap: 30px;
        margin-top: 40px;
    }

    .pillar {
        background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.02);
        border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05);
        padding: 30px;
        border-radius: 12px;
        text-align: center;
        transition: transform 0.2s;
    }

    .pillar:hover {
        transform: translateY(-5px);
        background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.04);
    }

    .pillar .icon {
        font-size: 3rem;
        margin-bottom: 20px;
    }

    .pillar h3 {
        color: #fff;
        margin-bottom: 10px;
    }

    /* Ranking Explainer */
    .rankings-explainer {
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 60px;
        background: linear-gradient(
            90deg,
            rgba(253, 185, 49, 0.05) 0%,
            transparent 100%
        );
        padding: 60px;
        border-radius: 20px;
        border-left: 4px solid #fdb931;
    }

    .dummy-badge {
        background: linear-gradient(135deg, #ffd700 0%, #fdb931 100%);
        color: #1a1a1a;
        padding: 20px 40px;
        border-radius: 12px;
        font-weight: 700;
        font-size: 1.5rem;
        font-family: var(--font-serif);
        box-shadow: 0 10px 30px rgba(253, 185, 49, 0.2);
    }

    .dummy-badge span {
        font-size: 2.5rem;
        font-weight: 900;
    }

    .branding-note {
        font-size: 0.9rem;
        color: var(--text-muted);
        font-style: italic;
        margin-top: 1rem;
    }

    /* Content Enrichment Styles */
    .content-block {
        margin-bottom: 80px;
    }

    .content-block.alt-bg {
        background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.02);
        padding: 60px;
        border-radius: 20px;
        border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05);
    }

    .section-title {
        font-size: 2.2rem;
        font-family: var(--font-serif);
        margin-bottom: 40px;
        color: #fff;
        text-align: center;
    }

    .section-intro {
        text-align: center;
        max-width: 700px;
        margin: 0 auto 40px;
        font-size: 1.1rem;
        color: var(--text-secondary);
    }

    /* Timeline */
    .timeline {
        position: relative;
        max-width: 800px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding-left: 20px;
        border-left: 2px solid rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.3);
    }

    .timeline-item {
        position: relative;
        margin-bottom: 40px;
        padding-left: 30px;
    }

    .timeline-item::before {
        content: "";
        position: absolute;
        left: -26px;
        top: 0;
        width: 10px;
        height: 10px;
        background: var(--accent-purple);
        border-radius: 50%;
        box-shadow: 0 0 10px var(--accent-purple);
    }

    .timeline-item .year {
        display: block;
        font-size: 0.9rem;
        font-weight: 700;
        color: var(--accent-purple);
        margin-bottom: 8px;
    }

    .timeline-content h4 {
        font-size: 1.3rem;
        color: #fff;
        margin-bottom: 8px;
    }

    /* Board Grid */
    .board-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
        gap: 24px;
    }

    .board-member {
        background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.03);
        padding: 30px;
        border-radius: 16px;
        border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05);
    }

    .member-role {
        font-size: 0.8rem;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 0.1em;
        color: var(--accent-purple);
        margin-bottom: 8px;
    }

    .board-member h4 {
        font-size: 1.2rem;
        color: #fff;
        margin-bottom: 12px;
    }

    /* Integrity Steps */
    .integrity-steps {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
        gap: 30px;
        margin: 40px 0;
    }

    .step {
        text-align: center;
    }

    .step-num {
        display: bock;
        font-size: 3rem;
        font-weight: 900;
        color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
        margin-bottom: 10px;
    }

    .step h4 {
        font-size: 1.2rem;
        color: #fff;
        margin-bottom: 10px;
    }

    .integrity-note {
        background: rgba(220, 38, 38, 0.1);
        border: 1px solid rgba(220, 38, 38, 0.2);
        padding: 20px;
        border-radius: 8px;
        text-align: center;
        color: #fca5a5;
        font-size: 1rem;
    }

    .partners-list {
        list-style: none;
        padding: 0;
        max-width: 600px;
        margin: 0 auto;
    }

    .partners-list li {
        padding: 16px;
        border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05);
        color: var(--text-secondary);
    }

    .partners-list strong {
        color: #fff;
        margin-right: 8px;
    }

    @media (max-width: 768px) {
        .about-container {
            padding: 0 16px 60px;
        }
        h1 {
            font-size: 2.5rem;
        }
        .hero {
            padding: 60px 0;
        }
        .grid-2 {
            gap: 40px;
        }
        .stat-box {
            flex-direction: column;
            gap: 30px;
        }
        .rankings-explainer {
            flex-direction: column;
            padding: 30px;
            text-align: center;
        }
    }
</style>
